subsection.def:
dispose (處置), in relation to premises, includes granting a
                                right to occupy the premises, and any reference to acquiring
                                premises shall be construed accordingly;

employment agency (職業介紹所) means a person who, for
                                profit or not, provides services for the purpose of finding
                                employment for workers or supplying employers with workers;

genuine occupational
                                        qualification (真正的職業資格) means genuine occupational qualification as
                                construed in accordance with section 12(2);

paragraph.content:
a brother or sister (whether of full blood or half
                                                blood) of the person or of the spouse or the spouse
                                                of such a brother or sister;

subsection.def:
responsible body (負責組織), in relation to an
                                educational establishment, means the body specified in column 2 of
                                        Schedule 1 opposite that establishment;

subparagraph.content:
which is such that the proportion of persons who are pregnant who can
                    comply with it is considerably smaller than the proportion of persons who are
                    not pregnant who can comply with it;

is such that the proportion of women who are breastfeeding and can
                        comply with it is considerably smaller than the proportion of persons who
                        are not breastfeeding and can comply with it;

paragraph.content:
in the way he affords her access to opportunities for promotion, transfer
                    or training, or to any other benefits, facilities or services, or by refusing or
                    deliberately omitting to afford her access to them;

subsection.def:
intern (實習人員) means a
                person who is engaged by another person for an internship but is not an employee of
                that other person;

paragraph.content:
a period of work the completion of which is required for attaining a
                        professional or academic qualification and includes a pupillage;
                        or

subsection.def:
volunteer (義工)
